  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Top, tail, peel and dice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1686066937591-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1686066937591-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1686066937591-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1686066937591-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1686066937591-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, add the<strong> diced carrot </strong>and reduce the heat to very low, then cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1686066943482-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1686066943482-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1686066943482-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1686066943482-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1686066943482-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> and <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>soy sauce</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) in a bowl</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken breast portion[s] </strong>and give everything a good mix up until fully coated</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1686066947585-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1686066947585-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1686066947585-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1686066947585-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1686066947585-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated chicken</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden</p><p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli relish</strong> and 30ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[45ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[60ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>in a bowl<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1686066951810-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1686066951810-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1686066951810-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1686066951810-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1686066951810-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is golden, add the<strong> sliced garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min or until slightly softened</p><p>Add a couple of splashes of <strong>water</strong> and the <strong>sweet chilli sauce </strong>to the pan and cover with a lid</p><p>Cook for a further 10-12 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1686066955942-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1686066955942-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1686066955942-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1686066955942-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1686066955942-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them to refresh them</p><p>Once the rice is cooked, add your<strong> refreshed peas</strong>, <strong>black sesame seeds</strong> and <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> and mix everything together – this is your <strong>veg-packed rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1686066959511-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1686066959511-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1686066959511-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1686066959511-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1686066959511-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>chicken</strong> to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks – this technique is known as ‘pulling’</p><p>Return the <strong>pulled chicken</strong> with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> sweet chilli chicken breast</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if your sauce is looking a little thick!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1686066964352-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1686066964352-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1686066964352-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1686066964352-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1686066964352-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>veg-packed rice</strong> with the <strong>sweet chilli chicken breast</strong> over the top</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
